senses
  entry
    definition "a prominent attribute or aspect of something"
    examples ("the map showed roads and other features" "generosity is one of his best characteristics")
    id oewn-05858316-n
    partOfSpeech n
    synonyms (characteristic)
  entry
    definition "the characteristic parts of a person's face: eyes and nose and mouth and chin"
    examples ("an expression of pleasure crossed his features" "his lineaments were very regular")
    id oewn-05609513-n
    partOfSpeech n
    synonyms (lineament)
  entry
    definition "the principal (full-length) film in a program at a movie theater"
    examples ("the feature tonight is ‘Casablanca’")
    id oewn-06627379-n
    partOfSpeech n
    synonyms ("feature film")
  entry
    definition "a special or prominent article in a newspaper or magazine"
    examples ("they ran a feature on retirement planning")
    id oewn-06279437-n
    partOfSpeech n
    synonyms ("feature article")
  entry
    definition "(linguistics) a distinctive characteristic of a linguistic unit that serves to distinguish it from other units of the same kind"
    id oewn-05858739-n
    partOfSpeech n
    synonyms ("feature of speech")
  entry
    definition "an article of merchandise that is displayed or advertised more than other articles"
    id oewn-03330714-n
    partOfSpeech n
  entry
    definition "have as a feature"
    examples ("This restaurant features the most famous chefs in France")
    id oewn-02636270-v
    partOfSpeech v
    synonyms (have)
  entry
    definition "wear or display in an ostentatious or proud manner"
    examples ("she was sporting a new hat")
    id oewn-02637740-v
    partOfSpeech v
    synonyms (sport boast)
